README:
To study the analgesic effects of music in chronic pain we recruited 20 fibromyalgia (FM) patients and 20 matched healthy controls (HC), acquiring rs-fMRI with a GE 3T MRI scanner, before and after music or pink noise exposure for 5 minutes. Data also includes T1w and DWI sequences.

For details see the preprint.

Preprint: https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/230243v1

Functional connectivity of music-induced analgesia in fibromyalgia. Victor Pando-Naude, Fernando A. Barrios, Sarael Alcauter, Erick H. Pasaye, Lene Vase, Elvira Brattico, Peter Vuust, Eduardo A. Garza-Villarreal. doi: https://doi.org/10.1101/230243. Biorxiv.
